item.description:
arXiv:2502.07756v1 Announce Type: cross 
Abstract: We investigate the asymptotic behavior of the $\mathrm{SU}(2)$-Yang-Mills-Higgs energy $E(\Phi,A)=\int_M|d_A\Phi|^2+|F_A|^2$ in the large mass limit, proving convergence to the codimension-three area functional in the sense of De Giorgi's $\Gamma$-convergence. More precisely, for a compact manifold with boundary $M$ and any family of pairs $\Phi_m\in\Omega^0(M;\mathfrak{su}(2))$ and $A_m\in \Omega^1(M;\mathfrak{su}(2))$ indexed by a mass parameter $m\to\infty$, satisfying $$E(\Phi_m,A_m)\leq Cm\quad\text{and}\quad\lim_{m\to\infty}\frac{1}{m}\int_M(m-|\Phi_m|)^2=0,$$ we prove that the $(n-3)$-currents dual to $\frac{1}{2\pi m}\mathrm{tr}(d_{A_m}\Phi_m\wedge F_{A_m})$ converge subsequentially to a relative integral $(n-3)$-cycle $T$ of mass \begin{equation}
  \mathbb{M}(T)\leq \liminf_{m\to\infty}\frac{1}{4\pi m}E(\Phi_m,A_m), \end{equation} and show conversely that any integral $(n-3)$-current $T$ with $[T]=0\in H_{n-3}(M,\partial M;\mathbb{Z})$ admits such an approximation, with equality in the above inequality. In the special case of pairs $(\Phi_m,A_m)$ satisfying the generalized monopole equation $*d_{A_m}\Phi_m=F_{A_m}\wedge \Theta$ for a calibration form $\Theta\in \Omega^{n-3}(M)$, we deduce that the limit $\nu=\lim_{m\to\infty}\frac{1}{2\pi m}|d_{A_m}\Phi_m|^2$ of the Dirichlet energy measures satisfies $\nu\leq |T|$, with equality if and only if $T$ is calibrated by $\Theta$, giving evidence for predictions of Donaldson-Segal in the settings of $G_2$-manifolds and Calabi-Yau $3$-folds.
